                <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm mt-4 text-justify">My journey began with a B.Sc. in Plant Pathology from Zabol, followed by an M.Sc. in GIS-based plant disease mapping in Iran. I earned my Ph.D. in Plant Pathology Modeling at Lincoln University, New Zealand, under Susan Worner’s mentorship. My postdoctoral work at the University of Florida with Professor Ariena van Bruggen and Karen Garrett advanced my expertise in innovative research.</p>
